  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Jinja waste RWS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at solving the municipal solid waste problem in Jinja, a town in Uganda approximately 81 km east of the capital Kampala. It is located along the northern shores of Lake Victoria, near the source of the White Nile (see figure 1). Jinja Municipal Council has the responsibility of dealing with waste and keeping the municipality clean. In 2011, the Council has conducted an Environmental Impact Assessment for a proposed landfill and waste composting plant in a neighbouring village (Masese). This study indicates that only 45% of municipal waste is collected and disposed due to resource limitations. The remaining 55% of the waste is dumped in the Nile, which is negatively impacting water quality and leads to environmental degradation.     The Jinja Municipal Council is therefore searching for a private company/partner which can help them collect and treat the waste, as well as finance the investment by turning it into an income generating activity through a PPP tender. The D2B project aims at supporting the Jinja Municipal Council with additional studies that are needed like an  upgrade of the ESIA, a pre-feasibility (with focus on problem analysis, composition and volumes of waste) as well as providing assistance for preparing a tender for this project.</narrative>
  </description>
